reement where signatory parties concede allowances.     <br><br>The interesting part is copyright law, by legal definition only actual persons can legally be 'original creator' of a copyright work. Companies and commercial entities not being 'real person x' are never legally 'original authors of a copyright works' and will conventionally buy the 'rights' to publish under license' (ie. publication under a limited agreement) or have outright copyright 'assigned' (ie. sold to them) by a 'real person' presumably the rightful owner. The net effect is BSI is probably guilty of breaching Piracy laws since it has no legal business with Mythic and is not protected by Copyright or any other legal convention or commercial royalty either: it has no material legal precedence to proceed against Mythic over commercial property rights. <p><br><br><p><h1 align="CENTER"><font size=1> Kissane Riptrace - "The sword is mine, I know how to make it work"<br> (what does an autoattack button know?) </font></h1><br><align="center"><img src="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/halas_faction.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umahtanhonorshield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mahtan Honorshield</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/7/02 2:13:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8586.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.cd.chalmers.se/~mort/gifs/icons/hacker-inv.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The right to Ebay?  Mythic gets sued</span><hr size=1> If I remember it correctly, the guys at